properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 9 at 3:28PM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, south winds 20 to 25 kt with
gusts up to 35 kt and waves 7 to 10 feet. For the Gale Watch,
northeast winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts up to 45 kt and waves 5
to 8 feet possible.

* WHERE...Lake Michigan from Seul Choix Point to Rock Island
Passage 5NM offshore to Mid Lake and Lake Michigan South of a
line from Seul Choix Point to the Mackinac Bridge and North of
a line from Charlevoix MI to South Fox Island 5NM offshore.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until midnight CST tonight. For
the Gale Watch, from Saturday afternoon through late Saturday
night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST TONIGHT... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
